# trivy config (misconfiguration) waivers — accepted-by-design for this demo.
# Each entry documents WHY the finding is accepted; the trivy-config gate
# (make trivy-config, in static-check) blocks any NEW HIGH/CRITICAL misconfig.

# KSV0014 — gitea container readOnlyRootFilesystem=false.
# Gitea (rootless) writes runtime state to its working tree (SQLite DB lives on a
# PVC, but the image also writes to paths outside the PVC at startup). Enforcing a
# read-only root FS would require enumerating + emptyDir-mounting every such path
# and risks breaking the DB-backed demo. Accepted for the demo; revisit if gitea
# is hardened for production.
AVD-KSV-0014

# KSV0041 — Traefik ClusterRole has access to 'secrets'.
# An ingress controller must read Kubernetes Secrets to serve TLS certificates and
# to back auth middleware; this is Traefik's standard (upstream-published) RBAC.
# The permission is get/list/watch, not cluster-admin. Accepted as inherent to the
# ingress-controller role.
AVD-KSV-0041
